quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Attributes[/h1]

We can manipulate attributes assigned to HTML elements easily through jQuery.
[b]href[/b], [b]src[/b], [b]id, class[/b], [b]style [/b]are all examples of HTML attributes.

The [b]attr()[/b] method is used for getting the value of an attribute.
For Example:
[b]HTML:[/b] [code format="html" ]<a href="www.sololearn.com">
   Click here
</a> [/code]
[b]JavaScript:[/b] [code format="js" codeId="1104"]$(function() {
  var val = $("a").[b]attr[/b]("href");
  alert(val);
});
// alerts "www.sololearn.com"[/code]
[note]In the code above we selected and alerted the value of the [b]href [/b]attribute of the <a> element.[/note]

